# Yarn Package Manager Rules

## Package Manager Preference

- Always use `yarn` instead of `npm` for all package management operations
- Use `yarn add` instead of `npm install` for adding packages
- Use `yarn add --dev` instead of `npm install --save-dev` for dev dependencies
- Use `yarn remove` instead of `npm uninstall` for removing packages
- Use `yarn` instead of `npm install` for installing all dependencies

## Script Execution

- Use `yarn run <script>` or `yarn <script>` instead of `npm run <script>`
- Use `yarn dev` instead of `npm run dev`
- Use `yarn build` instead of `npm run build`
- Use `yarn test` instead of `npm run test`

## Lock File

- Always commit `yarn.lock` to version control
- Never commit `package-lock.json` if it exists
- Use `yarn.lock` for dependency resolution

## Commands Translation

- `npm install` → `yarn`
- `npm install <package>` → `yarn add <package>`
- `npm install --save-dev <package>` → `yarn add --dev <package>`
- `npm uninstall <package>` → `yarn remove <package>`
- `npm run <script>` → `yarn <script>`
- `npm ci` → `yarn install --frozen-lockfile`
- `npm update` → `yarn upgrade`

## Docker and CI/CD

- Use `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` in production builds
- Use `yarn` in Dockerfile instead of `npm install`
- Update CI/CD scripts to use yarn commands
